WHO   — THERMODYNAMICS OF COMPUTATION — a life-science sphere — the life/hardware bridge
WHAT  — Information is physical. Every bit your laptop — or your brain — erases must pay a fixed tax in heat. This is the bedrock beneath all the others: why computing costs energy, and why the most efficient computer might have to be alive.
